                                "byte_start": 89902,
                                "byte_stop": 114039,
                                "text": "Justice Breyer has the opinion of the court in two cases this morning."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 6.027,
                        "stop": 172.487,
                        "byte_start": 114039,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15139,
                            "name": "Stephen G. Breyer",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/stephen_g_breyer",
                            "last_name": "Breyer",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2785,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 775890000,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Bill Clinton",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2785"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32682,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 49908,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/stephen_g_breyer_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 7777,
                            "identifier": "stephen_g_breyer"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 6.027,
                                "stop": 16.694,
                                "byte_start": 114039,
                                "byte_stop": 156775,
                                "text": "The first is called Global Crossing v. Metrophones, and it begins with telephone deregulation which allowed callers a choice of what long distance carrier they want."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 16.694,
                                "stop": 28.213,
                                "byte_start": 156775,
                                "byte_stop": 202855,
                                "text": "But sometimes they go a pay-phone, and the pay-phone company would connect them not with the long distance carrier that the caller wanted but with the company that the pay-phone operator wanted."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 28.213,
                                "stop": 30.646,
                                "byte_start": 202855,
                                "byte_stop": 212573,
                                "text": "Well Congress thought that was a bad idea."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 30.646,
                                "stop": 44.212,
                                "byte_start": 212573,
                                "byte_stop": 266803,
                                "text": "So, they passed a law and they said that the pay-phone company has to connect to however the caller wants connected to, whatever carrier, and moreover has to be for free, you don\u2019t have to put $0.25 in the box."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 44.212,
                                "stop": 48.377,
                                "byte_start": 266803,
                                "byte_stop": 283417,
                                "text": "At that point the pay-phone company said, well who is going to pay us for the call."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 48.377,
                                "stop": 76.013,
                                "byte_start": 283417,
                                "byte_stop": 393967,
                                "text": "So Congress passes another law and says let the FCC work that out, and the FCC tried to work it out over a couple of years, and finally what they said was, well here is who pays, the caller connects to a particular carrier through the pay-phone, then the carrier pays, $0.24 a call, or whatever they agree upon and the carrier can charge the ultimate customer with his long distance bill."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 76.013,
                                "stop": 85.736,
                                "byte_start": 393967,
                                "byte_stop": 432942,
                                "text": "Now apparently after that some carriers still wouldn\u2019t turnover the $0.24 to the pay-phone operator, atleast that\u2019s what the pay-phone operator will say."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 85.736,
                                "stop": 102.333,
                                "byte_start": 432942,
                                "byte_stop": 499293,
                                "text": "So, the pay-phone operators, some of them, or one of them anyway went to the FCC, and the FCC issued an order saying that you have to pay, and if you don\u2019t it is unreasonable practice under Section 201(b)."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 102.333,
                                "stop": 123.077,
                                "byte_start": 499293,
                                "byte_stop": 582258,
                                "text": "Later the pay-phone operators said they are still not paying us, so they brought a suit in Federal Court, under a different Section 207 which seems linked to \u00a7201(b) and the only question before us is whether they can bring that suit in Federal Court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 123.077,
                                "stop": 159.286,
                                "byte_start": 582258,
                                "byte_stop": 727081,
                                "text": "Well ultimately what we say it is ultimately because it takes a while to explain this case, ultimately what we say is, well \u00a7207 if you read the words is linked to violations of \u00a7201(b), and what we have here is a regulation under \u00a7201(b) which says, when you don\u2019t pay for that call, you don\u2019t pay the pay-phone operator, you have committed an unreasonable practice that seems to us like a violation of \u00a7201(b), it says you can bring the suit for a violation of \u00a7201(b) its reasonable for them to say that, bring the suit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 159.286,
                                "stop": 164.909,
                                "byte_start": 727081,
                                "byte_stop": 749546,
                                "text": "Now, that\u2019s the opinion of the court, we affirm the Ninth Circuit similar determination."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 164.909,
                                "stop": 172.487,
                                "byte_start": 749546,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Scalia has filed a dissenting opinion, and Justice Thomas has filed a dissenting opinion."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
